qas.question: The Times began producing what kind of non-newspaper product in 1895?
What publisher prints The Times atlas?
What is the name of The Times' atlas?

answers.text: The Times Comprehensive Atlas of the World

context: Times <a0_0>Atlases<a0_0/> have been produced since 1895. They are currently produced by the Collins Bartholomew imprint of <a1_0>HarperCollins Publishers<a1_0/>. The flagship product is <a2_0>The Times Comprehensive Atlas of the World<a2_0/>.
